  "text": "Filter and ReRank use the document entropy for a query-independent document quality measure [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The fraction of stopwords in the corpus that appear on the page, and the ratio of stopwords to nonstopwords on the page, were shown to be even more effective as document-quality measures for Web retrieval [CITATION_3] ; and, the most effective quality measures among those explored [CITATION_4] . (Here, a term is considered a stopword if it is among the 100 most frequent alphanumeric terms in the corpus [CITATION_5] .)",
